<term-sec id="id-9b6546da-c8a8-4651-faf0-d860d15246f2"><tbx:termEntry xmlns:tbx="urn:iso:std:iso:30042:ed-1"><tbx:langSet xml:lang="en"><tbx:definition><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5a3582f6-3d37-4d74-b706-e6c7e4e5896f" timestamp="1656530805133"?>any <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5a3582f6-3d37-4d74-b706-e6c7e4e5896f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="9998d748-e84a-4135-dcde-5868d38c454c" timestamp="1666863431385"?>conscious or unconscious <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9998d748-e84a-4135-dcde-5868d38c454c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="7a380242-5850-4c3a-d8da-44ddcccdf4f2" timestamp="1656530805133"?>act, gesture, visual representation, spoken or written words, practice or behaviour based upon the idea that a person or a group of persons is inferior because of their gender, which occurs in the public or private sphere, whether online or offline, with the purpose or effect of:<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="7a380242-5850-4c3a-d8da-44ddcccdf4f2"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="9459555e-c1aa-4f64-a28b-631a93e14de3" timestamp="1667333183147"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="9459555e-c1aa-4f64-a28b-631a93e14de3"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="6b792631-e94b-46f6-b591-357d83c6d17c" timestamp="1656530805133"?>violating the inherent dignity or rights of a person or a group of persons; or<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="6b792631-e94b-46f6-b591-357d83c6d17c"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="8ac82b8c-23e8-416e-f236-e755eb619af1" timestamp="1667333194181"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="8ac82b8c-23e8-416e-f236-e755eb619af1"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5da354b6-67b9-4aac-995d-ade8bdef52f9" timestamp="1656530805133"?>resulting in physical, sexual, psychological or socio-economic harm or suffering to a person or a group of persons; or<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5da354b6-67b9-4aac-995d-ade8bdef52f9"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="b4fea86a-feea-4757-a285-5e3540773de2" timestamp="1667333185335"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b4fea86a-feea-4757-a285-5e3540773de2"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="5210d890-59a5-47db-94ee-866dc9a0e4ee" timestamp="1656530805133"?>creating an intimidating, hostile, degrading, humiliating or offensive environment; or<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="5210d890-59a5-47db-94ee-866dc9a0e4ee"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="4fd76c2a-7273-4f0d-9d26-723e8d6cd2b5" timestamp="1667333187210"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4fd76c2a-7273-4f0d-9d26-723e8d6cd2b5"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="43bf5716-1c2b-4f11-8279-369dd39d224f" timestamp="1656530805133"?>constituting a barrier to the autonomy and full realisation of human rights by a person or a group of persons; or<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="43bf5716-1c2b-4f11-8279-369dd39d224f"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="1b1646b2-666d-4508-c408-a0998ba065b6" timestamp="1667333205047"?> <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="1b1646b2-666d-4508-c408-a0998ba065b6"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="fc31ae2c-585d-4cae-9c6b-b48306c4fe23" timestamp="1656530805133"?>maintaining and reinforcing gender stereotypes<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="fc31ae2c-585d-4cae-9c6b-b48306c4fe23"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8763689" change-id="9f78685e-aa33-45bf-c978-88ad42c897d1" text=" " timestamp="1656530741728"?></tbx:definition><tbx:note><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="2a3c2d50-c9eb-4ac0-a590-648c5d6bea56" timestamp="1656530767388"?>sexism can include forms of indirect violence (hints, jokes, inappropriate and insistent comments or looks, etc.) or forms of exclusion (informal discussions about work that are not accessible to everyone, etc.)<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="2a3c2d50-c9eb-4ac0-a590-648c5d6bea56"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8763689" change-id="17390aba-b6f3-4249-fb57-1308c229645e" text=" " timestamp="1656530763420"?></tbx:note><tbx:note><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="b7a29571-a74b-429f-ddb9-4ad0d0fb8509" timestamp="1656530783363"?>sexism and sexist behaviour are perpetrated at the individual, institutional and structural levels, and experienced with detrimental effect at all three levels. At the structural level, sexism constitutes a barrier <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b7a29571-a74b-429f-ddb9-4ad0d0fb8509"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="2f0d54be-bf5c-4f2d-91b3-6ce3c14182dd" text="gender equality and empowerment of women and girls" timestamp="1666863458828"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="46d7f0ff-092c-4a31-e1c9-d12139e5050c" timestamp="1670332611319"?>to gender equality and to the empowerment of women and girls; whereas men and boys are also restricted in their capabilities by sexist stereotypes. <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="46d7f0ff-092c-4a31-e1c9-d12139e5050c"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="f8891cbf-e59b-4ea7-9c6c-94a579cad33a" text=". " timestamp="1670332619046"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="4a6794db-0dc6-4f1c-b3c9-7b1f0722c8e1" timestamp="1656530783363"?>Gender stereotypes and inherent biases shape norms, behaviour and expectations, and therefore lead to sexist acts<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4a6794db-0dc6-4f1c-b3c9-7b1f0722c8e1"?></tbx:note><tbx:note><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="138e75e5-c2cd-4d9a-e530-ea48557735d6" timestamp="1656530798049"?>sexism is a part of a continuum of violence, it contributes to create a climate which may constitute favourable ground to violence against women or gender-based discrimination<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="138e75e5-c2cd-4d9a-e530-ea48557735d6"?></tbx:note><tbx:tig><tbx:term><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8763689" change-id="dd40ded2-6cf7-412c-c80f-7ea65e4ccad5" timestamp="1656530744608"?>sexism<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="dd40ded2-6cf7-412c-c80f-7ea65e4ccad5"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8763689" change-id="46fe35f9-64f1-43c7-e5c2-f12e7175a8b9" text=" " timestamp="1656530743674"?></tbx:term><tbx:partOfSpeech value="noun"/><tbx:normativeAuthorization value="preferredTerm"/><tbx:termType value="fullForm"/></tbx:tig></tbx:langSet></tbx:termEntry></term-sec>